article.headline: Tennessee Tech 69, S. Utah 68
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. -- Will Barnes made a free throw with 6 seconds remaining to lift Tennessee Tech to a 69-68 win over Southern Utah on Saturday night. The Thunderbirds (1-2) cut Tennessee Tech's lead to 68-67 with 53 seconds left in the second half on Eules Thompson's 3-pointer. Tyler Quinney, who finished with 20 points and grabbed 10 rebounds, tied the score at 68 after making a free throw with 34 seconds left in the game. But with 6 seconds left, Thompson fouled Barnes to send him to the foul line. Barnes missed the first free throw but made his second attempt to lift the Golden Eagles (3-0) toward the victory. Daniel Northern scored 15 points and blocked three shots for Tennessee Tech. Darnell Lindsay had 11 points and seven rebounds, while Barnes added nine points. Davis Baker and Eules Thompson scored 16 points apiece for Southern Utah.
